numerical values, such as stock prices or housing prices. 6. Medical Diagnosis:
Assisting doctors in diagnosing diseases based on patient data.
Applications of Supervised Learning
Supervised learning algorithms are widely used across various industries and
domains. For instance, in finance, these algorithms are employed for fraud
detection and risk assessment. In healthcare, they aid in medical image analysis,
patient diagnosis, and personalized treatment recommendations. In retail,
supervised learning is utilized for demand forecasting, customer segmentation, and
recommendation systems. Furthermore, in autonomous vehicles, these algorithms
play a pivotal role in object recognition and decision-making. These examples
illustrate the diverse applications of supervised learning in addressing complex
problems and enhancing decision-making processes.
